    Class Description
    Action<T>
    An Action is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked synchronously similar to a regular Java method call.
    Action0
    An Action0 is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked synchronously similar to a regular Java method call.
    Action0Async
    An Action0Async is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked asynchronously in another thread.
    Action0AsyncSupport
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous actions.
    Action0ToAction0Async
    An adapter that converts a conventional Action0 to an Action0Async.
    Action0ToAsyncAction0
    An adapter that converts an Action0 to a new Action0, that makes an asynchronous calls to the original Action0 upon invocation.
    Action2<T1,​T2>

    An ActionAsync is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked asynchronously in another thread.
    ActionAsyncResult
    A ActionAsyncResult represents the result of an ActionAsync invocation.
    ActionAsyncSupport<T>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous actions.
    ActionToActionAsync<T>
    An adapter that converts a conventional Action or Consumer to an ActionAsync.
    ActionToAsyncAction<T>
    An adapter that converts an Action or Consumer to a new Action, that makes an asynchronous calls to the original Action0 upon invocation.
    AsyncExecutor
    This is a helper class that is used for the asynchronous invocation of actions and functions.
    AsyncFutureTask<R>
    This FutureTask subclass is used internally for the asynchronous invocation of actions and funcions and implements the interfaces FunctionAsyncResult and ActionAsyncResult so that it directly serves as return value for the asynchronous invocations and as parameter given to the callback methods.
    Event<T>
    An Event is a source of signals and/or information that can be observed by subscribing Consumer instances to it.
    Event0
    An Event0 is a source of signals that can be observed by subscribing Action0 instances to it.
    Event0AsyncAdapter
    The Event0AsyncAdapter is class that adapts an Event0Delegate to Event0AsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously.
    Event0AsyncDelegate
    An Event0AsyncDelegate implements Action0Async as well as Event0Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action0Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event0Delegate interface.
    Event0Caller
    The Event0Caller is a Event0Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to a single subscriber.
    Event0Delegate
    An Event0Delegate implements Action0 as well as Event0 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action0 interface to all subscribers of the Event0 interface.
    Event0Distributor
    The Event0Distributor is a Event0Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to multiple subscribers.
